title: Inside FIFA
snippet: An English FA administrator from Blackburn, Daniel Burley Woolfall was elected as President on 4 June 1906. A key aim during his presidency was to achieve uniform football rules on an international level and he played a prominent role in the drafting of FIFA's new constitution.

title: List of presidents of FIFA facts for kids
snippet: FIFA is the main organization that controls association football (soccer) around the world. Some presidents, like Daniel Burley Woolfall, Rodolphe Seeldrayers, and Arthur Drewry, passed away while they were still in office.
